COSTUME - Materials and Textures
 

This is the fourth drop-down menu found in the main Movieola titlebar.

To use this tool, move the mouse curser over the word "Costume" and
press the left mouse button. This will prompt a drop down menu with
the following selections:

	Costume:
		Color...
		Texture...
		Material...
		Material Palette...
		Photo-real Property...

After "Sculptor", "Costume" is the most often tool used in creating
photo-real objects in Movieola.

Each selection under the "Costume" menu (Color, Texture etc.)
functions only when an object is selected. They are used to set the
"costume" of an object. When invoked without an object selected, they
do not affect any object in the main scene.
